<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES62-5A, ES62-5D, ES67-5A AND
        ES67-5D - DISASSEMBLY - INPUT SHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After removing the main drive gear bearing cap from the transmission, place it on a
                workbench with the open side down. Tap the edges of the cap with a rubber mallet until the bearing race
                falls out. Remove the spacer and oil baffle. Also remove the oil seal and replace it with a new one (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301041">Figure 41</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301041" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301041" filename="../figg13/g1301041.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 41. Remove Spacer, Oil Baffle, and Oil Seal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the input shaft. The hole in the center allows lubricant to flow to the pocket
                bearing. Make sure it is free from contaminants and other obstructions (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301042">Figure 42</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301042" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301042" filename="../figg13/g1301042.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 42. Remove Input Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press the bearing off the shaft and replace it with a new one (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301043">Figure 43</hotlnk>). It is good practice to always replace bearings during
                service.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301043" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301043" filename="../figg13/g1301043.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 43. Press Bearing Off Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Wear safety glasses to prevent possible personal injury from flying metal pieces.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
